The Corporation;;90;;89;;NC;;This documentary begins with an unusual detail that came from the 14th Amendment: Under constitutional law, corporations are seen as individuals. So, filmmaker Mark Achbar asks, what type of person would a corporation be? The evidence, according to such political activists as Noam Chomsky and filmmaker Michael Moore and company heads like carpet magnate Ray Anderson, points to a bad one, as the film aims to expose IBM's Nazi ties and these large businesses' exploitation of human rights.;;Documentary;;Mark Achbar,Jennifer Abbott;;2004;;Milton Friedman,Samuel Epstein,Peter Drucker,Noam Chomsky,Chris Barrett,Maude Barlow,Ray Anderson,Mikela J. Mikael;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_corporation_2004